== 歷史 ==
從原始[[IPhone_(第一代)|第一代iPhone]]到[[iPhone_4S|iPhone 4S]]的推出，iPhone都是使用3.5英寸顯示屏—對比其競爭對手的旗艦手機所使用的屏幕還要小。[[iPhone_5|iPhone 5]]及其後繼產品的顯示屏更長，但其寬度與之前的型號相同，而對角線測量為4英寸。隨著蘋果公司從生產更大顯示屏手機的公司手中使智能手機市場佔有率下降，早在2014年1月就有報導顯示蘋果公司正準備推出新款iPhone機型，配備更大的4.7英寸及5.5英寸顯示屏的iPhone<ref name="wsj-bigphones">{{cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304856504579338611620927036|title=Apple iPhones to Come Out With Bigger Screens|work=[[Wall_Street_Journal|Wall Street Journal]]|date=2014-01-24|accessdate=2014-09-09|archive-date=2014-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141216024736/http://www.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304856504579338611620927036|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="wsj-bigbet">{{cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-suppliers-gear-up-for-large-screen-iphones-1405985788|title=Apple Readies a Big Bet on Big-Screen Phones|work=[[Wall_Street_Journal|Wall Street Journal]]|date=2014-09-09|accessdate=2016-09-09|archive-date=2019-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825112453/https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-suppliers-gear-up-for-large-screen-iphones-1405985788|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ars-taller">{{cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/apple/2012/09/iphone-5-a-little-bit-taller-a-little-bit-baller|title=iPhone 5: a little bit taller, a little bit baller|work=[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]]|date=2014-09-09|accessdate=2014-09-09|archive-date=2017-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710004443/https://arstechnica.com/apple/2012/09/iphone-5-a-little-bit-taller-a-little-bit-baller/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在揭幕之前的報告還推測蘋果公司可能會引入[[近場通訊|近距離無線通訊]]的[[流動支付|流動支付]]平台到新iPhone型號上，此項技術已被納入許多[[Android|Android]]手機中，惟用戶的採用率很低<ref name=cnet-mobilepayments>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnet.com/news/iphone-6-iwatch-to-use-nfc-tokens-for-mobile-payments-report|title=More signs point to mobile payments for iPhone 6 – and for an iWatch|work=[[CNET|CNET]]|date=2014-09-09|accessdate=2014-09-09|archive-date=2019-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825112508/https://www.cnet.com/news/iphone-6-iwatch-to-use-nfc-tokens-for-mobile-payments-report/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

